<br>
So you could cast Grasping root over and over on a mob, but you wouldn't be able to use Ensnaring Roots on it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uxendrix.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xendrix</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/29/02 2:24:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2802.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: my higher level root will not overwrite my lower level r</span><hr size=1> I think the root and the damage are viewed as 2 separate components.  It used to be our root was worthless because the mob would get rooted, and then the damage would be treated as a DD hit and break the root.  It was a great thing when they fixed this.<br>
<br>
Root cannot be refreshed while it is still up from my experience.  If you have a mob rooted with a 3 minute max root, you cannot recast root at 2:55 to extend the life of the root.  The root MUST break in order to refresh it.  The damage appears to no longer be viewed as a DD hit since it does not break the root, but the root portion of the spell is not refreshed, so in order for that to work, I would guess that it is being treated as 2 completely separate entities.<br>
<br>
How was that for long winded...<br>
<br>
 <p>-Galipure Stormdancer<BR>Sun Clan of Warriors<BR>Solusek Ro<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utatankawd.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tatankawd</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/29/02 5:41:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2802.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: my higher level root will not overwrite my lower level r</span><hr size=1> Xendrix,<br>
<br>
I do it all the time, use 56 root as a small DD to finish off a mob that's almost dead (and already rooted).  Any of our roots can overwrite themselves without the root breaking prior to that.  But no root can overwrite any other root.<br>
<br>
Oh yeah, I have done it with the Warden Symbol (Grasping Roots) on mobs the break root early.  I have occasionally just stood there and continually clicked it, rerooting every 4-5 seconds.<br>
<br>
Try it again and let us know.<br>
<br>
